functions.name: delegate
functions.desc:
Ask a capable helper for help looking up a piece of information or performing an action.
Do not simply repeat what the user said as instructions.
You should use this to break up complex user queries into multiple simpler steps.
NOTE: Helpers cannot see previous parts of your conversation.

instructions.description: Detailed instructions on what your helper should do to help you.

msg.content: Who were the first five provosts of the University of Pennsylvania (including any repetitions), and where were they born?
Who were the first five provosts of the University of Pennsylvania (including any repetitions), and where were they born?

The first five provosts of the University of Pennsylvania were:

1. William Smith (1727-1803) - Born in Aberdeen, Scotland.
2. George Whitefield (1714-1770) - Born in Gloucester, England.
3. William Smith (1727-1803) - Reappointed as the third provost after George Whitefield's brief tenure.
4. John Ewing (1732-1802) - Born in Cecil County, Maryland, USA.
5. Rev. John R. Burden (1745-1786) - Born in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, USA.
